measure end to end latency 
add latency measurement node (recommended)
Create a simple test node that:

Publishes a command to /cmd_vel with a timestamp
Subscribes to IMU data /imu/accel or /imu/gyro
Calculates delta between command sent → sensor response


Goal: 
Tuning Control Algorithms

Line following: If your camera processes at 28 Hz but motor commands lag by 200ms, the rover reacts to old vision data → poor tracking
PID tuning: Controller gains depend on loop timing. Variable latency breaks PID assumptions → unstable control


Debugging Performance Issues
Your system has:

Camera: 28 Hz
IMU: 20 Hz
LIDAR: 7 Hz
If latency is high, you can identify bottlenecks:

Is the RPi CPU overloaded?
Is the /cmd_vel callback blocking on I2C/serial communication?
Are there scheduling delays in ROS 2?


System Integration

Sensor-to-actuator loop: You need to know: "Camera sees line → process image → send steering command → motor moves" total time
If this loop is >100ms, you're reacting to stale data at any speed > 1 m/s


the hard real time is stopping before impact 
* everything needs to be at a frequencys os that the stopping before impact happens with time to collision figured out .


================================================================================
REAL-TIME PERFORMANCE TESTING & OPTIMIZATION PLAN
================================================================================

Phase 0: Baseline Vision Performance (FIFO Test)
-------------------------------------------------
Purpose: Establish performance ceiling for vision processing before ROS overhead

Test: SCHED_FIFO Hough line detection at multiple resolutions
Location: See README_FIFO_TEST.md in this directory

STATUS: ✓ COMPLETED - April 18, 2026

Results Summary:
  Resolution  | Mean Exec Time | Performance  
  ------------|----------------|-------------
  424×240     | 18.03ms       | ✓ EXCELLENT (recommended)
  640×480     | 58.42ms       | ⚠ MARGINAL (over 50ms target)

Key Findings:
  - Hough line detection at 424×240: 18ms (well under 50ms deadline)
  - Leaves 32ms headroom for ROS overhead + Python processing
  - Expected total camera→cmd_vel: 30-40ms (meets target)
  
Decision: Use 424×240 resolution for line following
  - Provides actual line geometry (vs just edges)
  - 2.5x slower than Canny but still real-time capable
  - Better accuracy for steering control

CSV Files Generated:
  ✓ fifo_realsense_houghlines_424x240.csv
  ✓ fifo_realsense_houghlines_640x480.csv


Phase 1-4: ROS End-to-End Latency Monitoring
---------------------------------------------
Purpose: Measure complete camera→motor latency in production ROS system

Approach: Non-invasive monitoring (all code in amy_test, no modifications to production)

Nodes to create:
  1. topic_rate_monitor.py - Measures publication rates and jitter
  2. vision_latency_monitor.py - Correlates camera frames to /cmd_vel
  3. motor_latency_monitor.py - Measures /cmd_vel → IMU response
  4. latency_aggregator.py - Combines data, computes total latency
  5. performance_logger.py - CSV logging for analysis
  6. latency_dashboard.py - Real-time terminal display
  7. automated_latency_test.py - Automated validation

STATUS: ✓ INFRASTRUCTURE COMPLETE - April 18, 2026

Implementation Summary:
  ✓ Custom messages created (LatencyStats.msg, RateStats.msg)
  ✓ All 7 monitoring nodes implemented
  ✓ Launch file with 3 modes (monitoring, dashboard, test)
  ✓ Packages built successfully (custom_messages, amy_test)
  
Location: ~/code/Copperbottoms/ros_ws/src/amy_test/
Documentation: See README_LATENCY_MONITORING.md

Launch Modes:
